15/11/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- President Ahmet Necdet Sezer met on Tuesday (November 14th) with visiting Macedonian counterpart Branko Crvenkovski.
They discussed potential areas of co-operation, particularly in the military arena.
Crvenkovski thanked Turkey for its past assistance in defence sector reforms, and especially for the education and training of more than 280 Macedonian Army officers.
He reiterated Macedonia's commitment to join NATO and sought Turkish support for obtaining an accession date at the Alliance's upcoming summit in Riga.
(Sabah - 15/11/06;
MIA, Makfax, Telma TV - 14/11/06)
